The '''scarlet-breasted flowerpecker''' ('''''Prionochilus thoracicus''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Dicaeidae]]. It is found in [[Brunei]], [[Indonesia]], [[Malaysia]], and [[Thailand]]. Its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]] and subtropical or tropical [[swamp]]s. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

